cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO

The paper deals with object detection from imagery using a CNN-based model, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The methodology involves a sparse distribution estimation scheme, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG). The paper also emphasizes reduced manual engineering, which is a characteristic of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model is scene adaptive, which suggests the use of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with region-of-interest estimation, which is a topic in robotics (cs.RO).
